WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.540
I'm very excited to give the talk on this newest kid on the block, the JNJ5322 tri-specific

00:00:08.540 --> 00:00:15.660
targeting CD3 positive T cells, BCMA and GPRC5D in multiple myeloma.

00:00:16.440 --> 00:00:17.440
These are my disclosures.

00:00:19.880 --> 00:00:22.680
So this molecule now has a name.

00:00:22.820 --> 00:00:23.620
It's the romantomic.

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:30.360
So romantomic is a tri-specific antibody that targets CD3 positive T cells and BCMA and

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:36.520
GPRC5D antigens, which are both very heavily expressed on plasmoplasts and plasma cells

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:37.920
in multiple myeloma patients.

00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:47.440
So the rationale for this drug is that targeting two antigens simultaneously with T cell redirection

00:00:48.260 --> 00:00:53.440
may increase the affinity of binding to the tumor, increase antitumor.

00:00:53.620 --> 00:01:03.200
activity by more comprehensively attacking the myeloma cells as it will cover cells that

00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:09.220
are expressing just BCMA and just GPRC5D and then dual expressing myeloma cells.

00:01:09.440 --> 00:01:16.880
And this, we think, possibly could overcome tumor heterogeneity and tumor loss-mediated

00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:20.760
mechanisms of resistance and further improve clinical outcomes.

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:23.480
The difference in this molecule is actually that...

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:31.060
it comprises novel binding domains and low CD3 affinity selected in vitro to enhance

00:01:31.060 --> 00:01:35.060
the on-tumor effects and minimize the off-tumor impacts.

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:45.740
So the phase one study of romantomic was discussed earlier by Dr. Vandenong in ASCO 2025, and

00:01:45.740 --> 00:01:50.540
this evaluated romantomic in triple class exposed, and actually in the United States,

00:01:50.540 --> 00:01:53.540
it also included triple class refractory multiple myeloma patients.

00:01:53.620 --> 00:02:01.940
And the key objectives were identifying the recommended phase two dose, safety profile and preliminary efficacy.

00:02:01.940 --> 00:02:07.940
And there were various dose expansion cohorts that are being looked at, at a dose of...

00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:14.380
evaluating a dose of 0.4 all the way up to 300 milligrams with Q2 or Q4 dosing.

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:18.840
They were all given subcutaneously, and ultimately we landed on a step-up dose of five milligrams one time prior to 100 milligrams Q4 dosing.

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:18.840
and ultimately we landed on a step-up dose of five milligrams one time prior to 100 milligrams Q4 dosing.

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:19.840
and ultimately we landed on a step-up dose of five milligrams one time prior to 100 milligrams Q4 dosing.

00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:21.840
and ultimately we landed on a step-up dose of five milligrams one time prior to 100 milligrams Q4 dosing.

00:02:21.840 --> 00:02:22.820
and ultimately we landed on a step-up dose of five milligrams one time prior to 100 milligrams Q4 dosing.

00:02:22.820 --> 00:02:26.920
milligrams Q4 weeks as the recommended phase 2 dose for further evaluation.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:36.560
The baseline characteristics for this trial is it included about 126 patients that actually

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:43.240
achieved remantamic, and the median age was 64 in the overall cohort, and about 31%, so one-third

00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:47.040
of the patients had high-risk cytogenetics, which is pretty much what we see in practice.

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:54.960
All 100% of the patients were triple-class exposed, and about 53% of the patients were

00:02:54.960 --> 00:03:02.620
triple-class refractory, and about 20% of the patients were both BCMA or GPR-C5D exposed,

00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:05.300
and 80% were GPR-C5D or BCMA-naive.

00:03:08.140 --> 00:03:13.900
So, the overall response rate, particularly at the APIT-2D dose and in patients that were

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:16.860
BCMA or GPR-C5D-naive, was a hopping.

00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:17.380
Was a hopping.

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:23.540
Was a hopping 100% in 27 patients that received this dose, with very high rates of VGPR or

00:03:23.540 --> 00:03:25.080
better of 96%.

00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:32.400
The median time to response was 1.2 months at a median follow-up of 12 months, and these

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:34.280
responses actually deepened with time.

00:03:34.460 --> 00:03:42.480
The subsequent results that were demonstrated at ASH 2025 by Dr. Krishnan further revealed

00:03:42.480 --> 00:03:47.360
a deepening of the responses, and a higher percentage of patients, about 89%.

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:48.980
So, we're at the same rate of 90% achieving CR or better.

00:03:50.940 --> 00:04:00.680
The PFS, the two-year, sorry, one-year PFS overall was 95% at the APIT-2D dose, and 74%

00:04:00.680 --> 00:04:02.840
in all the doses combined.

00:04:03.440 --> 00:04:08.940
And at 12 months, it was about 93%, and for that 18-month follow-up, still maintained

00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:10.540
responses at 80%.

00:04:10.540 --> 00:04:17.340
So, in terms of the safety profile, neutropenia was one of the main factors that we saw.

00:04:17.340 --> 00:04:24.300
Major hematologic adverse events noted in 42% at the APIT-2D dose, and about 31% of

00:04:24.300 --> 00:04:26.640
these patients had actually grade 3, grade 4 neutropenia.

00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:33.480
The incidence of infections was quite high, 81%, and about one-third of those patients,

00:04:33.580 --> 00:04:36.300
so 33%, still had grade 3, grade 4 infections.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:42.840
The incidence of CRS was, interestingly, 53%, and majority of it was all grade 1, grade

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:43.040
2.

00:04:43.160 --> 00:04:45.900
No grade 3, grade 4 CRS events were noted.

00:04:47.320 --> 00:04:51.560
The taste-related changes, which we see quite commonly in talcetamab, which is the other

00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:59.860
GPRC-5D binding Bispecific, was quite lower, so 58% in all grade 1 and grade 2.

00:05:00.220 --> 00:05:05.160
Similarly, nail-related and non-trash-skin-related toxicities were also in the range of 50% to

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:06.840
60%, all grade 1, grade 2.

00:05:06.980 --> 00:05:09.100
No grade 3, grade 4 events were noted.

00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:11.540
Oh, sorry.

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:16.940
So, there was one dose-limiting toxicity.

00:05:17.300 --> 00:05:22.740
It was observed in the RP2D cohort, which was neutropenia, and overall, five dose-limited

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:27.660
toxicities were observed in all of the doses, and there was actually one death, unfortunately,

00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:30.200
in the RP2D cohort because of pneumonia.

00:05:34.160 --> 00:05:39.780
So, the incidence of CRS was actually reduced to 20% with the use of prophylactic tocilizumab

00:05:39.780 --> 00:05:45.240
in the RP2D cohort, and all of it was grade 1, and no grade 3, grade 4 events were noted,

00:05:45.240 --> 00:05:47.240
and actually no incidence of ICANN.

00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:49.700
The incidence of ICANN was noted at the RP2D dose, which is quite impressive.

00:05:51.700 --> 00:05:54.980
Most of the infections that were noted were actually upper respiratory tract infections,

00:05:55.060 --> 00:06:03.140
about 39%, and only 3% of those were grade 3, grade 4 infections, and the incidence of

00:06:03.140 --> 00:06:05.720
hypogammaglobulinemia was still about 50%.

00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:11.960
Interestingly, in the follow-up results that were announced at ASH, the cumulative incidence

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:16.120
of grade 3 or grade 4 infections actually plateaued within the first year of the therapy

00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:17.140
at the RP2D dose.

00:06:17.140 --> 00:06:17.280
So, that's a good thing.

00:06:17.280 --> 00:06:22.360
No additional deaths due to infections occurred in the subsequent follow-up period, and especially

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:25.860
with the use of IVIG being incorporated in all these patients.

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:32.640
And also, in terms of the oral adverse events, which is a major limitation in using talcetamab,

00:06:33.340 --> 00:06:39.600
as we know, compared with TAL or the redirect study with use TAL and TEC together, a relatively

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:45.320
low incidence of oral treatment emergent adverse events was noted, and a shorter duration of

00:06:45.320 --> 00:06:47.260
these side effects of about 8 weeks.

00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:55.820
And unlike TAL, the mean weight loss over time was quite minimal at the RP2D dose, and

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:59.760
consistent with TAL, the changes in weight were actually irrespective of the changes

00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:00.480
in taste.

00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:09.940
So, in conclusion, romantomic with one step-up dose of 5 mg prior to the 100 mg Q4 subcutaneous

00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:15.520
dose was selected at the recommended phase 2 dose to be evaluated in further studies.

00:07:15.520 --> 00:07:17.100
It appeared to have a safe,

00:07:17.100 --> 00:07:23.500
or in fact an improved safety profile. Similar or improved safety profile as compared to other

00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:30.260
Bispecific directed against GPRC5D or BCMA. CRS events were low, mostly grade 1,

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:34.380
grade 2, and further reduced with the use of prophylactic TOSI, supporting the

00:07:34.380 --> 00:07:40.500
use of TOSI prophylactically in outpatient setting especially. We still struggled with

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:46.240
grade 3, grade 4 infection rate of about 33%, but this plateaued within the first year of therapy,

00:07:46.240 --> 00:07:47.080
and we still struggled with grade 3, grade 4 infection rate of about 33%.

00:07:47.080 --> 00:07:53.220
With incorporation of IVIG treatment, the Bispecific actually had an improved

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:59.800
oral adverse event profile with minimal to no weight loss over time, and with really good

00:07:59.800 --> 00:08:06.520
overall response rates of 100% and responses deepening over time, with a 12-month PFS of 93%

00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:15.160
and 18-month PFS of 80% in patients that were BCMA or GPRC5D naive. I think we have a very

00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:16.920
solid drug in our armamentarium.

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:23.060
As we try to cure multiple myeloma, and just highlighting the studies that are incorporating

00:08:23.060 --> 00:08:28.340
this tri-specific. So there's the phase 1 studies that we talked about, and then the phase 2 study

00:08:28.340 --> 00:08:33.420
with the trilogy 3, which is looking at this drug in a large number of patients in relapsed

00:08:33.420 --> 00:08:38.380
infecting myeloma, and then also trying to move this drug to the frontline settings and newly

00:08:38.380 --> 00:08:42.640
diagnosed myeloma in combination with DARA or LEN or POM. And then the phase 3 study,

00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:46.900
which is evaluating the tri-specific as compared to TEC. And that's all. Thank you.

00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:47.740
- Thank you.
